-- Popolare Milano sets terms of 500 mln euro rights issue
-- 
-- Wed Apr 30, 2014 12:26PM EDT
-- None



MILAN, April 30 (Reuters) - Italian cooperative lender Banca Popolare di Milano <PMII.MI> (BPM) said on Wednesday it would sell new shares for 0.43 euros each in a 500 million euro ($693.3 million) capital increase.

BMP said it will issue up to 1.162 billion new ordinary shares or nine new ones for every 25 already held.